description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE BE ADVISED THAT THIS POST IS CURRENTLY ONLY OPEN TO EMPLOYEES OF CPFT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting internal opportunity is available at Elizabeth House. We are currently looking to recruit an effective and efficient Band 5 Executive Assistant as part of the Administration Hub. This post supports the Service Director and Operational Managers for the Children, Young People and Families Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Executive Assistant, you will be required to under take project work, prepare presentation material, oversee emails, operate a comprehensive bring forward system, organise internal and external high profile meetings, taking, transcribing and distributing formal minutes at meetings across Cambridgeshire and also line manage Senior Administrators at Fulbourn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This full-time position working 37.5 hours, Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm and salary £24,907 - £30,615 depending on previous relevant NHS experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to interview via Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a strong team work ethic, sense of accountability, accompanied by an ability to work under considerable pressure at times. This post is open to professionals with the right attributes to enhance a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Catherine Mustoe, Directorate Operational Admin Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;catherine.mustoe@cpft.nhs.uk / 07580 857747&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
